<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861217-0054 </DOCNO><HL> MCI to Expand a ServiceAnd Reduce Its Price 30%</HL><DD> 12/17/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MCICTELECOMMUNICATIONS, BROADCASTING, TELEPHONE, TELEGRAPH (TEL) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   MCI Communications Corp. said it is expanding the capability of its high-speed terrestrial digital communications service, known as T-1, and reducing its price an average of 30%, effective Feb. 1.    The telecommunications concern said the service improvements and the price cuts were made possible by its extensive use of digital and fiber optic technology.    Other features available Feb. 1 include a fiber-only routing option with no monthly recurring charge, term discounts for one, three and five years and volume discounts for high-usage customers. T-1 service generally is used by large corporations for data, voice or video transmissions. </TEXT></DOC>